id: pm-yp56
title: "GH-588: pm comment --message exits 0 recording nothing — comment invocation without any comment text must fail fast"
description: "GitHub issue #588: --message on the comments command is the history-message flag, not comment text; an invocation carrying no comment source (no positional text, no --add, no stdin/file) exits 0 with count:0 and records nothing. Fix = fail fast with actionable guidance (use --add/positional/stdin) or at minimum warn that only a history message was recorded."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,cli,silent-failure
created_at: "2026-07-18T10:08:09.956Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T10:08:09.956Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Comment invocation with no comment text errors (or warns) with guidance naming --add/positional/stdin; exit code non-zero on the error path; contract + regression coverage; --message continues to set the history message when comment text is present
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
